        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2439832448" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12697375061220197902">Burton has created a diverse and fascinating cast of characters and 17th century Amsterdam with its many waterways, cobblestones and endearing as well as creepy and scary inhabitants comes to life like a detailed Brueghel painting depicting busy scenes set in Protestant Netherlands. Without wanting to give anything away from the intricate story line, I have to admit though that one aspect of the story was hugely unsettling for me. As much as homosexuality was punished hundreds of years ago becau</span>
  <span id="freeText12697375061220197902" style="display:none">Burton has created a diverse and fascinating cast of characters and 17th century Amsterdam with its many waterways, cobblestones and endearing as well as creepy and scary inhabitants comes to life like a detailed Brueghel painting depicting busy scenes set in Protestant Netherlands. Without wanting to give anything away from the intricate story line, I have to admit though that one aspect of the story was hugely unsettling for me. As much as homosexuality was punished hundreds of years ago because of pure ignorance and religious misguidance ... for me the book made me think that even today there are countries currently still stuck in the past judging other people’s sexual preferences in a barbaric manner. The other interesting theme in the book is how women could deal with their set roles, defying conventions without ruffling too many feathers and that this ultimately depended on an open mind and female complicity. </span>
  <a data-text-id="12697375061220197902" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
