  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1024843540" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1024843540" />
    <a title="Lisa" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/14819128-lisa"><img alt="Lisa" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1412502384p2/14819128.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1024843540?book_show_action=true">Aug 12, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Lisa" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Lisa" href="/user/show/14819128-lisa">Lisa</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9781447250890" href="/book/show/18047651-the-miniaturist">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/14819128-lisa?shelf=own">own</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/14819128-lisa?shelf=favourites">favourites</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/14819128-lisa?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/14819128-lisa?shelf=magical-realism">magical-realism</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/14819128-lisa?shelf=2014-reads">2014-reads</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/14819128-lisa?shelf=2017-reads">2017-reads</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1024843540" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7362747357562516131">This book is the fastest selling debut novel since &apos;Fifty Shades of Grey&apos;. Eleven big name publishers battled it out for the rights to its publication. It is one of the most hyped releases of 2014 and is currently outselling J K Rowling. With this in mind, I came into it with fairly high expectations. I was not disappointed. It was everything I was hoping for, an intriguing mix of mystery, love, secrets, betrayal, identity and revenge, all set against the backdrop of 17th century Amsterdam.<br/><br/>The s</span>
  <span id="freeText7362747357562516131" style="display:none">This book is the fastest selling debut novel since 'Fifty Shades of Grey'. Eleven big name publishers battled it out for the rights to its publication. It is one of the most hyped releases of 2014 and is currently outselling J K Rowling. With this in mind, I came into it with fairly high expectations. I was not disappointed. It was everything I was hoping for, an intriguing mix of mystery, love, secrets, betrayal, identity and revenge, all set against the backdrop of 17th century Amsterdam.<br /><br />The story centres upon eighteen year old Nella Oortman who arrives in Amsterdam from the country to take up residence in the home of the wealthy Brandt family. Nella was recently married to the head of the family, a VOC merchant by the name of Johannes, and is somewhat apprehensive about her new life in the city. Upon arrival, she finds her new home to be a less than welcoming place. Her new husband is distant, his sister unfriendly and their servants do not act in the way in which Nella expected them to. It soon becomes apparent that there are many secrets hidden within the Brandt household and when the titular miniaturist enters the story, things gradually start to spiral out of control. <br /><br />I really loved the writing in this book. Jessie Burton certainly knows how to set a scene and create atmosphere and her rich, evocative descriptions of seventeenth century Amsterdam and its inhabitants really do bring everything vividly to life for the reader. Plot wise, this book is very much like a dolls house. The longer and harder you look, the more you see and understand. There are plenty of twists, turns and revelations along the way, some of which you may guess and others you probably won't. I like to be surprised whilst reading and this book certainly surprised me on several occasions. I couldn't get enough of it. I just had to know what was going to happen next.<br /><br />There are plenty of fascinating characters to be found within these pages, some of whom you love, others who you hate. I particularly enjoyed the development of Nella throughout the course of the novel. Initially quite naive and out of her depth, she matures into a strong willed woman who is more than capable of standing up for herself and taking charge if needs be. I also liked watching how her relationships with the members of the Brandt household developed and changed as the story progressed. However, by far the two most interesting characters for me were her husband Johannes and his younger sister Marin. Johannes didn't feature quite as much as I expected him to but when he did, I found him to be an intriguing, likeable and sympathetic character. I found Marin to be somewhat grating initially. She just seemed to be unfriendly towards Nella for the sake of it. However, like the rest of the book, there is far more to her and her actions than first meets the eye and she ended up becoming one of my favourite characters. As for the miniaturist, to reveal too much would be to spoil so it's best to read the book for yourself in order to find out what their role in the story is.<br /><br />Overall, this was a fantastic book that I just had to rate 5 stars. It was a bit slow to start so some perseverance may be needed, and not all of the questions raised are answered but this did not affect my overall enjoyment at all. In certain aspects, this book is what you make it. I would highly recommend checking it out if you like well written historical fiction that is populated by some great characters, has plenty of twists, intrigue and suspense, a dash of mystery and a sprinkling of fantasy/magical realism. For me personally, this is a book that lived up to its hype. Jessie Burton is currently working on her second novel and I will be looking out for that with great interest.</span>
  <a data-text-id="7362747357562516131" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


